====Verb====
{{en-verb|wakes|waking|woke|past2=waked|woken|past_ptc2=waked}}

# {{lb|en|intransitive}} (often followed by ''[[up]]'') To stop [[sleep]]ing.
#: {{ux|en|I '''woke''' up at four o'clock this morning.}}
#* '''1898''', {{w|J. Meade Falkner}}, {{w|Moonfleet}} Chapter 4
#*: How long I slept I cannot tell, for I had nothing to guide me to the time, but '''woke''' at length, and found myself still in darkness.
# {{lb|en|transitive}} (often followed by ''[[up]]'') To make somebody stop sleeping; to [[rouse]] from sleep.
#* {{RQ:KJV|Zechariah|4|1||And the Angell that talked with me, came againe and '''waked''' me, {{...}}}}
#: {{ux|en|The neighbour's car alarm '''woke''' me from a strange dream.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive|figurative}} To put in motion or action; to arouse; to excite.
#* {{RQ:Milton Paradise Regained|Samson Agonistes|59|passage=Not for my life, leſt fierce remembrance '''wake''' / My ſudden rage to tear thee joint by joint.}}
#* '''1880''', {{w|John Richard Green}}, ''History of the English People''
#*: Even Richard's crusade '''woke''' little interest in his island realm.
# {{lb|en|intransitive|figurative}} To be excited or roused up; to be stirred up from a dormant, torpid, or inactive state; to be active.
#* {{RQ:Milton Paradise Lost|book=IX|lines=93–94|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=F08CAAAAQAAJ&pg=PP293|passage=and gentle Aires due at thir hour / To fan the Earth now '''wak'd''',}}
#* {{RQ:Keble Christian Year|volume=I|poem=Easter Day|page=146|passage=Then '''wake''', my soul, to high desires, / And earlier light thine altar fires: [...]}}
# To lay out a body prior to [[burial]] in order to allow family and friends to pay their [[last respects]].
# To watch, or sit up with, at night, as a dead body.
# To be or remain awake; not to sleep.
#* {{RQ:KJV|Ecclesiasticus|42|9||The father '''waketh''' for the daughter when no man knoweth, and the care for her taketh away sleepe;}}
#* {{RQ:Milton PL|book=3|lines=696–697|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=F08CAAAAQAAJ&pg=PP106|passage=And oft though wiſdom '''wake''', ſuspicion ſleeps / At wiſdoms Gate,}}
